    "Id": "chassisdef_ferdelance_FDL-2",
    "Name": "Fer-de-Lance",
    "Details": "Created during the heyday of the Star League era, the Fer-de-Lance is a 30 ton Cannopian BattleMech built by Majesty Metals and Manufacturing at their Canopus IV facilities. Surviving the succession wars mostly intact, the Fer-de-Lance is still produced in small quantities by MMM every year and features in most MAF light mech lances. The FDL-2 is built around a 240 rated XL engine and is armed with a pair of Medium lasers and a pair of Small Lasers. Sporting minor upgrades over the original FDL-1 model, the FDL-2 retains the same weapons loadout but compliments it with Jump Jets, a Beagle Active Probe and DHS.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Nimble</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 0.99</color></b>",
